import re
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.backends.backend_pdf import PdfPages
import numpy as np
from collections import defaultdict
import matplotlib.patches as mpatches
from matplotlib import rcParams
import gffutils
from utility_sj import parse_featurecounts_junctions, detect_novel_junctions, process_featurecounts_and_novel_junctions, plot_grid_for_aligners, extract_cig_junctions, extract_cig_junctions, process_featurecounts_baruzzo , extract_gtf_junctions, extract_custom_gtf_junctions
from utility_sj import plot_grid_for_aligners_2columns_deepSAP_vs_rest
from pdf2image import convert_from_path
from IPython.display import display, Image

MAPQ = "0"
sample = "SRR5280319"
featurecounts_file = f"/data/Benchmark/results/pHGG/analysis__GRCh38_GENCODE_r46/featureCounts/{sample}/counts_all_MAPQ{MAPQ}.jcounts"

orientations = "vertical"
output_pdf = f"/data/Benchmark/results/pHGG/analysis__GRCh38_GENCODE_r46/featureCounts/{sample}/pHGG_{sample}_MAPQ{MAPQ}_sj_scatterplots_{orientations}.pdf"

counted_junctions = parse_featurecounts_junctions(featurecounts_file)

novel_junctions = counted_junctions - gtf_junctions 

print(f"Processing pHGG {sample}")
print("GTF junctions:\t", len(gtf_junctions))
print("FC  junctions:\t", len(counted_junctions))
print("FC novel junctions:\t", len(novel_junctions))

df = process_featurecounts_and_novel_junctions(featurecounts_file, novel_junctions)

aligner_mapping = {
    'deepSAP': 'DeepSAP',
    'dragen': 'DRAGEN',
    'novoSplice': 'novoSplice',
    'star': 'STAR',
    'hisat2': 'HISAT2',
    'subjunc': 'Subjunc'
}

# Rename columns in the DataFrame using the aligner_mapping dictionary
df.rename(columns=aligner_mapping, inplace=True)

plot_grid_for_aligners_2columns_deepSAP_vs_rest(df, "DeepSAP", [ "DRAGEN", "novoSplice", "STAR", "HISAT2", "Subjunc"], output_pdf, log_scale=True, add_constant=1, limit=5, orient=orientations)

images = convert_from_path(output_pdf, dpi=300)  # save image to png then showing it
png_path = f"/data/Benchmark/results/pHGG/analysis__GRCh38_GENCODE_r46/featureCounts/{sample}/pHGG_{sample}_MAPQ{MAPQ}_sj_scatterplots_{orientations}.png"

resized_image = images[0].resize((images[0].width // 2, images[0].height // 2))

resized_image.save(png_path, 'PNG')

display(Image(png_path))
